{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3515"},"text":"§ 3515.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Security personnel at Agency installations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d4-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special policemen: functions and powers; regulations: promulgation and enforcement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Director may authorize Agency personnel within the United States to perform the same functions as officers and agents of the Department of Homeland Security, as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s1315/b/2"},"text":"section 1315(b)(2) of title 40","children":[],"tail":", with the powers set forth in that section, except that such personnel shall perform such functions and exercise such powers—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" within the Agency Headquarters Installation and the property controlled and occupied by the Federal Highway Administration located immediately adjacent to such Installation;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the streets, sidewalks, and the open areas within the zone beginning at the outside boundary of such Installation and property and extending outward 500 yards;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" within any other Agency installation and protected property;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824d9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" within an installation owned, or contracted to be occupied for a period of one year or longer, by the Office of the Director of National Intelligence; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824da-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/1/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the streets, sidewalks, and open areas within the zone beginning at the outside boundary of any installation or property referred to in subparagraph (C) or (D) and extending outward 500 yards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824db-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The performance of functions and exercise of powers under subparagraph (B) or (E) of paragraph (1) shall be limited to those circumstances where such personnel can identify specific and articulable facts giving such personnel reason to believe that the performance of such functions and exercise of such powers is reasonable to protect against physical damage or injury, or threats of physical damage or injury, to Agency installations, property, or employees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824dc-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to preclude, or limit in any way, the authority of any Federal, State, or local law enforcement agency, or any other Federal police or Federal protective service.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824dd-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The rules and regulations enforced by such personnel shall be the rules and regulations prescribed by the Director and shall only be applicable to the areas referred to in subparagraph (A), (C), or (D) of paragraph (1).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824de-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Penalties for violations of regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director is authorized to establish penalties for violations of the rules or regulations promulgated by the Director under subsection (a) of this section. Such penalties shall not exceed the maximum penalty authorized for a Class B misdemeanor under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3559"},"text":"section 3559 of title 18","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824df-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Identification","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Agency personnel designated by the Director under subsection (a) of this section shall be clearly identifiable as United States Government security personnel while engaged in the performance of the functions to which subsection (a) of this section refers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e0-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Protection of certain CIA personnel from tort liability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e1-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding any other provision of law, any Agency personnel designated by the Director under subsection (a), or designated by the Director to carry firearms under subparagraph (D) or (E) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3506/a/4"},"text":"section 3506(a)(4) of this title","children":[],"tail":", shall be considered for purposes of chapter 171 of title 28, or any other provision of law relating to tort liability, to be acting within the scope of their office or employment when such Agency personnel take reasonable action, which may include the use of force, to—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" protect an individual in the presence of such Agency personnel from a crime of violence;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide immediate assistance to an individual who has suffered or who is threatened with bodily harm; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e4-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prevent the escape of any individual whom such Agency personnel reasonably believe to have committed a crime of violence in the presence of such Agency personnel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Paragraph (1) shall not affect the authorities of the Attorney General under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2679"},"text":"section 2679 of title 28","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3515/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In this subsection, the term “crime of violence” has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s16"},"text":"section 16 of title 18","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd1e824e7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-20/ch227/s15"},"text":"June 20, 1949, ch. 227, § 15","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/tI/s140"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473, title I, § 140","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1973"},"text":"98 Stat. 1973","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/618/tIV/s401"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–618, title IV, § 401","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-11-08"},"text":"Nov. 8, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/3301"},"text":"98 Stat. 3301","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/107/tIV/s404"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–107, title IV, § 404","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-20"},"text":"Nov. 20, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/2260"},"text":"111 Stat. 2260","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/306/tVIII/s841/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–306, title VIII, § 841(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-27"},"text":"Nov. 27, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2432"},"text":"116 Stat. 2432","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/177/tIII/s377/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–177, title III, § 377(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 402, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-13"},"text":"Dec. 13, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/2630"},"text":"117 Stat. 2630","children":[],"tail":", 2631; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/dE/tLXIV/s6413"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, div. E, title LXIV, § 6413","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/2198"},"text":"133 Stat. 2198","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dF/tLXIII/s6303/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. F, title LXIII, § 6303(a)","children":[],"tail":", title LXIV, § 6414(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/3503"},"text":"136 Stat. 3503","children":[],"tail":", 3528; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/31/dG/tIII/s7331"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–31, div. G, title III, § 7331","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 2023","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/137/1045"},"text":"137 Stat. 1045","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dF/tLXV/s6502/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. F, title LXV, § 6502(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1620"},"text":"139 Stat. 1620","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd1e824e8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd1e824e9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idd1e824ea-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to section 403","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":" of this title prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/tI/s140"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473, title I, § 140","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/618/tIV/s401"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–618, title IV, § 401","children":[],"tail":", added substantially identical sections 15 to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-20/ch227"},"text":"act June 20, 1949, ch. 227","children":[],"tail":". This section is based on the section 15 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-20/ch227"},"text":"act June 20, 1949, ch. 227","children":[],"tail":", as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/618"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–618","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd1e824eb-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Installation” for “Compound” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2023—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/31"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–31","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the maximum penalty authorized for a Class B misdemeanor under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3559"},"text":"section 3559 of title 18","children":[],"tail":"” for “those specified in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s1315/c/2"},"text":"section 1315(c)(2) of title 40","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a)(1)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s6303/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 6303(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (C), added subpar. (D). Former subpar. (D) redesignated (E)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(E). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s6303/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 6303(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (D), redesignated subpar. (D) as (E) and inserted “or (D)” after “in subparagraph (C)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s6303/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 6303(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “or (E)” for “or (D)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s6303/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 6303(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “in subparagraph (A), (C), or (D)” for “in subparagraph (A) or (C)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s6414/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 6414(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “designated by the Director to carry firearms under subparagraph (D) or (E) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3506/a/4"},"text":"section 3506(a)(4) of this title","children":[],"tail":",” for “designated by the Director under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3506/a/4"},"text":"section 3506(a)(4) of this title","children":[],"tail":" to carry firearms for the protection of current or former Agency personnel and their immediate families, defectors and their immediate families, and other persons in the United States under Agency auspices,” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Subsec. (a)(1)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s6413/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 6413(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “500 yards;” for “500 feet;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s6413/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 6413(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “500 yards.” for “500 feet.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/177/s377/b/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–177, § 377(b)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “officers and agents of the Department of Homeland Security, as provided in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s1315/b/2"},"text":"section 1315(b)(2) of title 40","children":[],"tail":",” for “special policemen of the General Services Administration perform under the first section of the Act entitled ‘An Act to authorize the Federal Works Administrator or officials of the Federal Works Agency duly authorized by him to appoint special policeman for duty upon Federal property under the jurisdiction of the Federal Works Agency, and for other purposes’ ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s318"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 318","children":[],"tail":"),”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/177/s377/b/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–177, § 377(b)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s1315/c/2"},"text":"section 1315(c)(2) of title 40","children":[],"tail":"” for “the fourth section of the Act referred to in subsection (a) of this section ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s318c"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 318c","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/177/s402"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–177, § 402","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (a)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/306"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–306","children":[],"tail":" struck out par. (5) which read as follows: “Not later than "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-12-01"},"text":"December 1, 1998","children":[],"tail":", and annually thereafter, the Director shall submit a report to the Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence of the House of Representatives and the Select Committee on Intelligence of the Senate that describes in detail the exercise of the authority granted by this subsection, and the underlying facts supporting the exercise of such authority, during the preceding fiscal year. The Director shall make such report available to the Inspector General of the Central Intelligence Agency.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/107/s404/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–107, § 404(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), inserted “(1)” after “(a)”, substituted “powers—” for “powers only within Agency installations, and the rules and regulations enforced by such personnel shall be rules and regulations promulgated by the Director.”, and added subpars. (A) to (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2) to (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/107/s404/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–107, § 404(3)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (2) to (5)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idd1e824ec-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd1e824ed-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Designation of Headquarters Compound of Central Intelligence Agency as the George Bush Center for Intelligence","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Reference to the headquarters compound of the Central Intelligence Agency deemed to be a reference to the George Bush Center for Intelligence, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/272/s309"},"text":"section 309 of Pub. L. 105–272","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3501"},"text":"section 3501 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
